cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MA, cs.CV, cs.GR

This paper presents a dockerized version of StarCraft: Brood War, which is commonly used as a domain for AI research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI. The paper also discusses the pre-installed collection of AI development tools, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of computer vision techniques to extract information from the game, which could place it in the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the deployment of StarCraft AIs on multiple hosts, which could be related to cs.GR (Graphics).
